FBIS4-6458 "dreas077_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 North Korea KCNA Reports Anti-U.S. Rallies in Moscow KCNA Reports Anti-U.S. Rallies in Moscow SK2004153394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1516 GMT 20 Apr 94 SK2004153394 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Rallies protesting the U.S. pressure on the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the deployment of Patriot missiles in South Korea were held on April 10 in front of the embassies of the United States and Japan and the South Korean "embassy" in-Moscow, according to a report. Participating in the rallies were a secretary of the central committee, and the first organisational secretary of the Moscow committee, of the All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party, and people from different walks of life. The speakers at the rallies sharply denounced the United States and its followers, Japan and the South Korean authorities, for carrying the situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war on the pretext of the DPRK's "nuclear development", and demanded that the United States stop at once its interference in the internal affairs of Korea and new war provocation manoeuvres. They demanded an immediate withdrawal of the U.S. troops and nuclear weapons from South Korea and expressed full support to the Korean people in their struggle for peace of the country and its peaceful reunification. Statements and appeals denouncing the anti-DPRK moves of the United States, Japan and the South Korean authorities were published at the rallies.
